bug.short_desc: [abrt] xorg-x11-server-Xorg: FlushClient(): Xorg killed by SIGABRT
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I use Fedora 25 with all updates. Within an hour, the X server crashed on me twice. In both cases I had Thunderbird, Xournal, Dolphin and Okular open. It crashed once when I opened a new email in Thunderbird. It crashed another time when I opened another PDF file from Dolphin that spawns a new instance of Okular.
It seems that opening a new window makes it crash.
Here is the extract from the log that I got by extracting it with `journalctl -b` on another virtual terminal:
